[[File:SpcialProgressIndexVsEnergInOilPerDay2.png|thumb|upright=2|Social Progress Index vs Energy Use per capita. [[List of countries by Social Progress Index]].]] [[File:Energy-consumption-per-capita-2003.png|thumb|upright=2|A map depicting [[world energy consumption]] per capita based on 2003 data from the [[International Energy Agency]].]] [[File:World Map - Energy Use 2013.png|thumb|upright=2|A map depicting world energy consumption per capita based on 2013 data from the World Bank<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://data.worldbank.org/data-catalog/world-development-indicators|title=World Development Indicators Data |website=World Bank|access-date=2016-09-17}}</ref>]] [[File:Energy Use per Capita.png|thumb|upright=2|The World Bank : Kilograms of oil equivalent (2011)]] [[File:Earth_lights_vs_population_density.png|thumb|upright=2|Map of Earth lights (green channel) vs population density (red channel)]] This is a '''list of countries''' by total [[energy consumption]] per capita. This is not the consumption of end-users but all energy needed as input to produce fuel and electricity for end-users. It is known as [[total primary energy supply]] (TPES), a term used to indicate the sum of production and imports subtracting exports and storage changes (see also [[Worldwide energy supply]]). Numbers are from The World Bank - World Development Indicators.<ref name=wb2 />
The data is given in [[kilogramme of oil equivalent|kilogrammes of oil equivalent]] per year, and [[gigajoule]]s per year, and in watts, as average equivalent power. ;Notes on conversions: * 1 [[Kilogram oil equivalent|kg of oil equivalent]] (kgoe) = 11.63 kWh or 1 kWh = 0.08598 kgoe<ref>[https://www.unitjuggler.com/convert-energy-from-koe-to-kWh.html?val=10000 convertenergy from koe to kWh]</ref> * 1000 kgoe = 42 GJ * 1 GJ/a = 31.7 W average * 1 W average = 8.76 kWh per year (365 × 24 Wh per year)
