{{Redirect|Macchia}} [[image:Macchia01.jpg|thumb|220px|Low Maquis in Corsica]] [[image:Gutturu mannu g4.jpg|220px|thumb|High ''macchia'' in Sardinia]] '''Maquis''' ([[French language|French]]) or '''macchia''' ([[Italian language|Italian]]: ''macchia mediterranea'') is a [[shrubland]] [[biome]] in the [[Mediterranean region]], typically consisting of densely growing [[evergreen]] [[shrub]]s. <ref name=MarCavShrublands>{{cite book|title=Habitats of the world.|date=2006|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|location=New York|isbn=978-0761475231|pages=488, 492–493|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RNvzrqO0HuEC&pg=PA491&dq=maquis+shrubland&hl=de&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjB8YKmgK3JAhVM7hoKHQNTAE8Q6AEINzAE#v=onepage&q=maquis%20shrubland&f=false|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=SoilOfItaly>{{cite book|last1=Costantini|first1=Edoardo A.C. (ed.)|last2=Dazzi|first2=Carmelo (ed.)|title=The soils of Italy|date=2013|publisher=Springer|location=Dordrecht|isbn=978-9400756410|pages=30,78,80,83,255,283|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MbhEAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA86&dq=macchia+degradation&hl=de&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_yeHfgK3JAhUJLhoKHUo-BqsQ6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=macchia%20erosion&f=false|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=RSA-17>{{cite book|last1=Aranda Jimenez|first1=Gonzalo|last2=Montón Subías|first2=Sandra|last3=Sánchez Romero|first3=Margarita|title=The Archaeology of Bronze Age Iberia: Argaric Societies (Routledge Studies in Archaeology)|date=December 10, 2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1138821330|pages=63–64|edition=Routledge Studies in Archaeology (Book 17)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7DlWBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA63&dq=maquis+shrubland&hl=de&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjB8YKmgK3JAhVM7hoKHQNTAE8Q6AEIWjAJ#v=snippet&q=shrubland&f=false|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=CretanLS>{{cite book|last1=Rackham|first1=Oliver|authorlink = Oliver Rackham|last2=Moody|first2=Jennifer|title=The making of the Cretan landscape|date=1994|publisher=Manchester University Press|location=Manchester|isbn