'''Nirmal Shah''' is an [[environmentalist]], writer, fund raiser and civic leader from the [[Seychelles]],<ref name="shah1">(30 September 2010) [http://www.africagoodnews.com/brand-africa/travel-and-tourism/2159-seychelles-launch-worlds-first-carbon-neutral-reserve.html Seychelles launch world's first carbon neutral reserve], ''Africa The Good News'', November 12, 2010</ref> and director of Nature Seychelles.<ref name="ref2">(2 March 2007) [http://www.seychellesweekly.com/March%202,%202007/Page%202.html Eden Island in the International News], ''Seychelles Weekly'', Retrieved November 12, 2010</ref>

Shah, who was educated in [[India]] and the [[United States]], advocates for conservation of [[biodiversity]], [[sustainable development]] and civil society participation through local and regional [[NGO]]s, international forums and the media. He is the founder of the Wildlife Clubs of Seychelles, the major youth NGO based in schools and institutions of higher learning.

