'''Pigeon River''' may refer to the following streams in the U.S. state of Michigan:
* [[Pigeon River (Huron County, Michigan)]], in [[Huron County, Michigan|Huron County]] in [[the Thumb]] of Michigan, flowing west and north into the Saginaw Bay of Lake Huron<ref>{{gnis|634858|Pigeon River (Lake Huron)}}</ref> * [[Pigeon River (Mullett Lake)]], with headwaters in Otsego County, flowing mostly northward through Montmorency and Cheboygan counties into [[Mullett Lake]]<ref>{{gnis|634857|Pigeon River (Mullett Lake)}}</ref> ** South Branch Pigeon River, a tributary of the Pigeon River in Otsego County<ref>{{gnis|638301|South Branch Pigeon River}}</ref> * [[Pigeon River (Ottawa County, Michigan)]], rising in [[Ottawa County, Michigan|Ottawa County]]'s [[Olive Township, Ottawa County, Michigan|Olive Township]], flowing east to west into Pigeon Lake and then Lake Michigan at Port Sheldon<ref>{{gnis|634856|Pigeon River (Lake Michigan)}}</ref> * [[Pigeon River (St. Joseph River)]], rising in northern Indiana and flowing mostly westward through southern Michigan into the [[St. Joseph River (Lake Michigan)|St. Joseph River]] near the Michigan-Indiana border northwest of Elkhart, Indiana<ref>{{gnis|441121|Pigeon River (St. Joseph River)}}</ref>
